@startuml
actor Student
participant "SubmissionService" as SubmissionService
participant "AuditService" as Audit
participant "ICryptoService" as Crypto
database DB
actor Lecturer
actor Admin

Student -> SubmissionService : submit verified or failed submission event
SubmissionService -> Audit : record(actionType, actor, entity, details)
Audit -> Audit : build canonical payload\n(actionType, actorUserId, entityType, entityId, timestamp, details)
Audit -> DB : load previous audit record integrity value (optional)
DB --> Audit : previousIntegrityValue
Audit -> Crypto : computeAuditMac(canonicalPayload, previousIntegrityValue)
Crypto --> Audit : integrityValue (HMAC-SHA-256)
Audit -> DB : append AuditLog\n+ integrityValue\n+ previousIntegrityValue
DB --> Audit : audit entry stored
Audit --> SubmissionService : audit recorded

note right of Audit
The implemented backend uses `AuditService.record(...)`
for append-oriented writes and computes an
HMAC-SHA-256 integrity value over a canonical payload.
end note

note right of DB
The model is append-oriented and stores
`previousIntegrityValue` for simple chaining.

The repo does not currently expose a public
`/api/audit/...` review endpoint for lecturers or admins.
Current audit review evidence comes from tests and
DB inspection rather than a dedicated REST flow.
end note

note over Lecturer,Admin
Lecturer/admin audit consumption is still a deferred
operational/reporting concern, not an implemented
application endpoint in the current codebase.
end note
@enduml
